name: Onna
description:
onna is a type of female warrior who belongs to the Japanese aristocracy.  These women were involved in combat, generally alongside the male samurai.  They were members of the bushi (samurai) class in feudal Japan and were trained in the use of weapons to protect their homes, families, and honor in times of war.
